{"ts": "2026-06-09T17:17:05.427520+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile the findings.\n\n---\n\n## Building the Flutter (mobile) project for the web target\n\nThis repository (\"inKino\") has three sub-projects:\n\n| Folder | Framework | Purpose |\n|--------|-----------|---------|\n| `core/` | Pure Dart | Shared business logic |\n| `mobile/` | **Flutter** | Android / iOS (and, with web enabled, Flutter for Web) |\n| `web/` | AngularDart | Separate PWA at inkino.app |\n\nTo get a **Flutter** web build that lands in `build/web/`, you work from the `mobile/` Flutter project. The README's **\"Building the project\"** section tells you about a prerequisite rename, and the CI script (`ci-script.sh`) shows the exact dependency-fetch commands. Here are the commands in order:\n\n---\n\n### (a) Enable Flutter web tooling\n\n```bash\nflutter config --enable-web\n```\n\n> *(On Flutter ≥ 2.x web is enabled by default, but this command is still the canonical way to ensure it.)*\n\n---\n\n### One-time prerequisite (from the README – rename the sample config file)\n\n```bash\ncd core/lib/src && mv tmdb_config.dart.sample tmdb_config.dart && cd ../../..\n```\n\nWithout this step the project will fail to compile (the file `tmdb_config.dart` is imported but only a `.sample` exists in the repo).\n\n---\n\n### (b) Fetch dependencies\n\n```bash\ncd core && pub get && cd ..\ncd mobile && flutter pub get\n```\n\nThis mirrors the CI script: it resolves packages for the shared `core` library first, then for the `mobile` Flutter app (which depends on `core` via a relative path).\n\n---\n\n### (c) Produce a release web build\n\n```bash\ncd mobile && flutter build web --release\n```\n\nThe output (HTML, JS, assets) will be placed in **`mobile/build/web/`**.\n\n---\n\n### Summary – copy-paste block\n\n```bash\n# (a) Enable Flutter web\nflutter config --enable-web\n\n# Prerequisite: rename sample config\ncd core/lib/src && mv tmdb_config.dart.sample tmdb_config.dart && cd ../../..\n\n# (b) Fetch dependencies\ncd core && pub get && cd ..\ncd mobile && flutter pub get\n\n# (c) Release web build → mobile/build/web/\ncd mobile && flutter build web --release\n```\n\n> **Note:** The `web/` directory at the repo root is the *AngularDart* PWA (built with `webdev`, not Flutter). If you actually want *that* app, the README says to run `pub get` then `webdev serve` (or `webdev build` for a production bundle) inside the `web/` directory. That build produces a different output path, not `build/web/`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1763, "prompt_tokens": 16478, "total_tokens": 18241, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 1157, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 11584}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "mimo-v2.5-pro", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "d0aa17d968fe43f4a0c743221af1dcc4", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ead62-ab20-7902-a5c0-1486aa7888dc-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 16478, "output_tokens": 1763, "total_tokens": 18241, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 11584}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 1157}}}}]}}}
